-- Lincoln National Executive Vice President Crawford to Step Down
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-01-18T21:32:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/lincoln-national-executive-vice-president-crawford-to-step-down.html
Lincoln National Corp. (LNC) , the insurer
that repaid a $950 million government bailout, said that
Frederick Crawford, executive vice president of corporate
development and investments, will resign this month.  Crawford will leave the Radnor, Pennsylvania-based insurer
on Jan. 20, according to a filing today with the U.S. Securities
and Exchange Commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in  New York  at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  